13. VERIFICATION.profile.md

## Expected Layout

- src/: application package and CLI entrypoint location.
- tests/: pytest tests.
- docs/: project policies and handoff notes.

## Allowed Work

- Documentation changes.
- Python source changes when the target project phase allows implementation.
- pytest test additions or updates when in coding phases.
- CLI smoke check definition or execution when commands are project-defined.

## P1 Template Boundary

This template does not create Python code, pytest files, package metadata, or CLI commands. It only defines profile guidance.

## Verification Defaults

- pytest for unit and integration-style checks.
- CLI smoke check for the primary command path.
- Acceptance trace update for requirement-to-evidence mapping.

## Safety Defaults

- No private raw input in tests or fixtures.
- No credentials in CLI arguments, examples, docs, or logs.
- Side effects are dry-run first unless the project explicitly defines safe local behavior.
